Step 3- Create New Workspace

Create New workspace

Note: Sample was done with the name Alumni workspace

Creating New Workspace will help:

- to protect the Power BI Published report against unauthorized users

- to organize the Power BI Published report

- to access it easily by the users  

How to create

- Go to My Workspace icon and click on Create a workspace

- Give the workspace name" Alumni" as a sample in the dialogue box 

- Choose Private, if it is planned only approved member can see what is inside

or Public, if it is planned any one can see what is inside . (in this case choose Public)

- Choose Members can edit Power BI content, but there is an option Members can only view Power BI content



Creating workspace in Power BI 

https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/power-bi/service-create-workspaces
